# Trivy waivers — the ONLY sanctioned waiver path (SH-1 acceptance). Each entry is a
# base-image (distroless) OS-package CVE not reachable from KEEL's own code; fixes are
# pending in the distroless python3-debian12:nonroot base and clear automatically when
# the base updates. Re-review on every base bump; nothing here waives a finding in
# KEEL code (those must be fixed, never ignored).

# cpython http.client excessive read-buffering DoS. KEEL makes only client-side HTTP
# calls via httpx (to model providers); the viewer uses Starlette/uvicorn, not
# stdlib http.client servers. Fixed upstream in 3.11.2-6+deb12u7 (not yet in base).
CVE-2025-13836

# OpenSSL heap use-after-free in PKCS7_verify(). KEEL never calls PKCS7_verify; TLS to
# providers is handled by httpx/OpenSSL's standard paths. Fixed in openssl
# 3.0.20-1~deb12u2 (not yet in base).
CVE-2026-45447
